      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "The most likely are all scratched. TE ELCEE (8) is second-up for the Currie yard. There was a lot to like about his hard-fighting effort at Toowoomba on debut (slow track) and he was expected to go close there first up but disappointed. Prepared to forgive that, and he's a decent chance with the extra fitness. INSAIN LADY (10) is a leader who was tracking well before being outgraded at Eagle Farm. Comes back 200m and will be tough to peg back. CLIODHNA MAEVE (4) has been knocking on the door and the longer sprint will suit. He gets a key gear switch and should be right in it. FARNESINA (5) resumes and has been racing in town. Has a handy 2kg claim and can come back improved for the Munce yard.",
